{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow the flying of Suffrage flag as a symbol of women's equality",
        "additional_details": "This petition calls for an amendment to the Town and Country Planning (Control of Advertisements) Regulations. A new category of flag should be added to those recognised as having the deemed consent of the local planning authority to be flown:\r\n\r\n* the Suffrage flag (three horizontal equal stripes of purple, white and green).\r\n\r\nThis would place the flag alongside the Rainbow and NHS flags as a mark of civic pride, formally recognising and celebrating an integral part of British history.",
        "background": "Since its introduction in 1908, the Suffrage flag of the Women's Social and Political Union has attained iconic status as a symbol of women's equality. Catalogued under WOA T52 of the Parliamentary Collection, it deserves the same legal recognition granted to e.g. the Rainbow and NHS flags.",
